For a rectangle with dimensions 200x200 to be positioned in the lower right corner of a 1280x800 screen, you would calculate:

X position = screen width - rectangle width = 1280 - 200 = 1080
Y position = screen height - rectangle height = 800 - 200 = 600

So the coordinates would be:
x = 1080
y = 600

This positions the rectangle so its upper-left corner is at (1080,600), making the rectangle appear in the bottom-right corner of the screen with 200 pixels of width and height.

Visual representation:
```
(0,0)        Screen (1280x800)         (1280,0)
   +--------------------------------+
   |                                |
   |                                |
   |                      (1080,600)|
   |                          +---+ |
   |                          |   | |
   |                          |   | |
   |                          +---+ |
   +--------------------------------+
(0,800)                        (1280,800)
```
